.0.0.0.1">October 11, 2013 7:50 am</time></div></div><div class="col col-sm-5" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1"><div class="social-share-top" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0"><div class="component-social-share default" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0"><div class="share-item facebook" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fa-gqa-with-karen-russell-novelist-gq-correspondent-and-newly-minted-macarthur-genius&amp;t=A%20GQ%2BA%20with%20Karen%20Russell%3A%20Novelist%2C%20GQ%20Correspondent%2C%20and%20Newly%20Minted%20MacArthur%20Genius" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fa-gqa-with-karen-russell-novelist-gq-correspondent-and-newly-minted-macarthur-genius&amp;t=A%20GQ%2BA%20with%20Karen%20Russell%3A%20Novelist%2C%20GQ%20Correspondent%2C%20and%20Newly%20Minted%20MacArthur%20Genius" target="_blank" aria-label="Facebook" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0"><span class="icon" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0.0"></span><span class="label" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0.1">Facebook</span></a></div><div class="share-item twitter" data-href="https://twitter.com/share?text=A%20GQ%2BA%20with%20Karen%20Russell%3A%20Novelist%2C%20GQ%20Correspondent%2C%20and%20Newly%20Minted%20MacArthur%20Genius&amp;via=GQMagazine&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fa-gqa-with-karen-russell-novelist-gq-correspondent-and-newly-minted-macarthur-genius" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter"><a href="https://twitter.com/share?text=A%20GQ%2BA%20with%20Karen%20Russell%3A%20Novelist%2C%20GQ%20Correspondent%2C%20and%20Newly%20Minted%20MacArthur%20Genius&amp;via=GQMagazine&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fa-gqa-with-karen-russell-novelist-gq-correspondent-and-newly-minted-macarthur-genius" target="_blank" aria-label="Twitter" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter.0"><span class="icon" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter.0.0"></span><span class="label" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter.0.1">Twitter</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><h2 class="dek" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.3"></h2><div class="body-text" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4"><div class="embed image" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.0"><figure class="embedded-image" data-type="image"><div class="image-content"><div class="component-rendition"><div class="component-image loaded"><span><img src="http://media.gq.com/photos/558288f3e52bc4b477a97083/master/w_806/blogs-the-feed-2013-10-11-karren-russel-blog.jpg" alt="blogs-the-feed-2013-10-11-karren-russel-blog.jpg"></span></div></div><div class="component-social-share default"><div class="share-item facebook" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fa-gqa-with-karen-russell-novelist-gq-correspondent-and-newly-minted-macarthur-genius&amp;t=blogs-the-feed-2013-10-11-karren-russel-blog.jpg"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fa-gqa-with-karen-russell-novelist-gq-correspondent-and-newly-minted-macarthur-genius&amp;t=blogs-the-feed-2013-10-11-karren-russel-blog.jpg" target="_blank" aria-label="Facebook"><span class="icon"></span><span class="label">Facebook</span></a></div><div class="share-item pinterest" data-href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fa-gqa-with-karen-russell-novelist-gq-correspondent-and-newly-minted-macarthur-genius&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F558288f3e52bc4b477a97083%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2Fblogs-the-feed-2013-10-11-karren-russel-blog.jpg&amp;description=blogs-the-feed-2013-10-11-karren-russel-blog.jpg"><a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fa-gqa-with-karen-russell-novelist-gq-correspondent-and-newly-minted-macarthur-genius&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F558288f3e52bc4b477a97083%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2Fblogs-the-feed-2013-10-11-karren-russel-blog.jpg&amp;description=blogs-the-feed-2013-10-11-karren-russel-blog.jpg" target="_blank" aria-label="Pinterest"><span class="icon"></span><span class="label">Pinterest</span></a></div></div></div></figure></div><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.1">Miami native Karen Russell is a novelist, writing professor, <a href="http://www.gq.com/news-politics/newsmakers/201210/one-eyed-matador">sometimes <em>GQ correspondent</em></a>, and, now, a certified, undeniable genius. Maybe you heard. Last month, when the MacArthur Foundation announced its twenty-four &amp;#x201C;Genius&amp;#x201D; grants, our young Brooklynite was on the list. Her writings &amp;#x201C;blend fantastical elements with psychological realism and classic themes of transformation and redemption,&amp;#x201D; said the committee. &amp;#x201C;She depicts in lyrical, energetic prose an enchanting and forbidding landscape and delves into subcultures rarely encountered in contemporary American literature.&amp;#x201D;</p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.2">(And not to honk our own horn here, but Russell is the second <em>GQ</em>er to land a MacArthur. Correspondent George Saunders [whom she cites as an influence] was awarded Genius status in 2006.)</p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.3">Contacted the day after, Russell was still in shock and (she said) not ready for any sort of a press conference. But after some time, a bit of pleading, and the <em>Breaking Bad </em>series finale, Ms. 305 agreed to a morning interview that became an afternoon interview after she forgot her cell phone.</p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.5"><strong>GQ: When and where did you get the Call?</strong></p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.6"> <strong>Karen Russell:</strong> I got the call on a Wednesday, right at dusk. I came back to my studio and there was a call from a weird area code on my voicemail; given the freakily unfamiliar area code, I assumed it was from my car insurance company. My car was stolen last month, and I&amp;#x2019;ve spent time on the phone with &amp;#x201C;Monica&amp;#x201D; the insurance adjustor. The woman on my voicemail was &amp;#x201C;Cecilia,&amp;#x201D; not &amp;#x201C;Monica,&amp;#x201D; but she spoke in a tone of professional friendliness and authority, which is basically the USAA tone. I thought about letting it go, but I didn&amp;#x2019;t want trouble with USAA.</p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.7"><strong>Did you know the Foundation was looking your way?</strong></p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.8"> I truly had no idea. No one can apply, and no one knows they are being considered. I could not be more grateful&#x2014;I&amp;#x2019;m still shell-shocked, I think. On their website they say, &amp;#x201C;The award is speculative; it does not recognize lifetime achievement but invests in individual potential.&amp;#x201D; And it feels really wonderful, to think that these seasoned gamblers at the MacArthur are going to bet on you and your work.</p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.9"><strong>Did you call back or let it go?</strong></p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.a"> I called back, standing in this foreign kitchen, on week two of my Brooklyn tenancy, and Cecilia [Conrad, VP of the MacArthur Fellows program] asked me if I knew about the MacArthur Grant. A friend of mine had just been joking, when R. Kelly dropped sex &amp;#x201C;Genius,&amp;#x201D; that R. Kelly should get the MacArthur.</p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.b"><strong>Then what?</strong></p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.c"> Cecilia told me the details of the award, but not before I did the <em>Price is Right</em> reaction. I was like &amp;#x201C;No no no <em>no</em>.&amp;#x201D; Then I learned I was on speakerphone. There was a room full of people listening in. These people comprised the MacArthur Selection Committee. Then I started breathing like a fat man on a trampoline, and babbling my thanks. I think I avoided expletives, but I can&amp;#x2019;t be certain. &amp;#x201C;Happy&amp;#x201D; is too simple a modifier for my feelings upon receipt of this baffling, surreal, hilariously great news.</p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.d"><strong>Don&amp;#x2019;t they make you wait a week or something?</strong></p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.e"> They let you tell one person, but I cheated a little bit and told my brother and sister. I wanted to tell them both at once, but I couldn&amp;#x2019;t get Gchat to show both their faces. When I told them, they kept me grounded by listing one hundred of the dumbest things I&amp;#x2019;ve ever said and done. Then my brother cranked DJ Laz, in tribute to Miami. It&amp;#x2019;s a tricky Miss Manners situation, it&amp;#x2019;s hard to know how to celebrate an impossible moment like that, on Gchat.</p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.f"><strong>Do you get a pin or a medal or some plaque or something?</strong></p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.g"> It would be great if you got a brass &amp;#x201C;M&amp;#x201D; breastplate, or a scepter of some kind that would visually establish you as a non-dummy, and maybe translate into subway seats and free drinks, but I don&amp;#x2019;t think you get anything material. (What you do get is so mind-bogglingly generous that I am still in gratitude-anaphylactic shock). Even without MacArthur armor or a monogrammed sweater, I am so honored.</p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.h"><strong>What were your first sober thoughts?</strong></p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.i"> Right away I was converting the money into time. Time that I can dedicate to writing. I hope to write more non-fiction for you guys, but at the moment I&amp;#x2019;m back to imaginary worlds. I like fictionland. There&amp;#x2019;s no fact-checking there and it&amp;#x2019;s not an ethical breach to swap in new settings and rearrange chronologies and shape your characters&amp;#x2019; dialogue. So even though writing a new story is always a struggle for me, at least in fictionland I&amp;#x2019;m less likely to be sued.</p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.j"><strong>How will this award affect you as a writer?</strong></p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.k"> I also love the use of that word &amp;#x201C;speculative&amp;#x201D; to modify the prize, because as a fiction writer, I really do feel that the prize opens up so many new horizons. And at the same time that I feel free to pursue all kinds of wild projects, in fictionland, in our brick-and-mortar everyday, I&amp;#x2019;m just so happy to be able to pay the rent and maybe get a stable home base set up. I&amp;#x2019;ve been in Berlin and then Philly and in January I&amp;#x2019;m going to Iowa, and I just moved into a studio sublet in Brooklyn. Just orbiting the tarmac, trying to land the plane.</p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.l"><strong>Is there anything bad about getting a half-million dollars for being a genius?</strong></p><p data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.4.m"> One immediate consequence of receiving the MacArthur is that I now view the telephone as an almost occult object, a portal through which the most astonishing news manifests itself. Good news! I think that&amp;#x2019;s the surprise, when it&amp;#x2019;s so much easier to expect disaster. The day after I heard from Cecilia, a D.C. area code called, and I laughed, realizing that a part of me now believed anything was possible. Maybe it was Obama. Maybe it was Abraham Lincoln, calling to request stoppage of the Booth assassination. It&amp;#x2019;s going to be a long life now, primed to expect shockingly good news from unknown numbers, when it&amp;#x2019;s much more likely to be a wrong number, somebody calling for their drunk uncle in Hialeah, or demanding stuffed-crust pizza.</p></div><div class="grid" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.5"><div class="row" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.5.0"><div class="col col-sm-15" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.5.0.0"><div class="component-topics" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0"><ul data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0"><li data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-0"><a href="http://www.gq.com/search?tags=Karen&#32;Russell" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-0.0">Karen Russell</a></li><li data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-1"><a href="http://www.gq.com/search?tags=MacArthur&#32;Genius&#32;Awards" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-1.0">MacArthur Genius Awards</a></li><li data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-2"><a href="../search?tags=Pop%2520Culture" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-2.0">Pop Culture</a></li></ul></div></div><div class="col col-sm-5" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.5.0.1"><div class="social-share-bottom" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0"><div class="component-social-share default" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0"><div class="share-item facebook" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fa-gqa-with-karen-russell-novelist-gq-correspondent-and-newly-minted-macarthur-genius&amp;t=A%20GQ%2BA%20with%20Karen%20Russell%3A%20Novelist%2C%20GQ%20Correspondent%2C%20and%20Newly%20Minted%20MacArthur%20Genius" data-reactid=".21s8f1v9q80.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fa-gqa-with-karen-russell-novelist-gq-correspondent-and-newly-minted-macarthur-genius&amp;t=A%20GQ%2BA%20with%20